rComments: She is disorganized and her Blackboard page was a mess. She interrupts students during class discussions and often talks about content that is unrelated to the course, which is frustrating. Readings did not apply to the course description.
When I took it in fall of 2012, it was utterly a waste of time for serious students I'm afraid. Hate to be so brutally honest. I think it was the 1st time she taught it though.

Dr. Bonin genuinely cares about her students. To succeed and get an A in her class PARTICIPATE. Speak up, debate, attend the things she schedules. If you get an unsatisfactory mark in the first assignment, schedule a meeting with her for the second one and ask her guidance. She is willing and helpful. She likes when you write a lot. :) VS
Professeure passionnée par la matière du cours et ça se voit dans son enseignement. Disponible pour ces étudiants.

She knows what she wants and she tells her students. Do as she tells you and you'll be all rigth.  Follow the steps and be clear in you essays and all will be well. Demanding teacher but easy to follow..

Comments and feedback were unhelpful and page limits were unreasonably low. Directions on projects were minimal. Hold onto all the assignments she returns to you -- she tried to stiff me for almost 20% of my final grade because she couldn't keep track of things on her own. Lectures were boring and she was occasionally rude. Self-centered.
